      "content": "A loud humming sound from your AC unit with a non-spinning fan could be due to a few things, such as a loose fan blade, a faulty motor, or a problem with the compressor. It's generally not recommended to inspect electrical components on your own, as it can be dangerous. I would suggest contacting a professional HVAC technician to take a look at it to ensure your safety and the proper functioning of your AC unit. In the meantime, you can try to make sure the unit is not under direct sunlight or exposed to strong winds, as these could be contributing factors to the issue.",
